    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="727"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">617.003/242: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 12, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Your telegram No. 3, January 10, 6 p.m. You should inform the Nicaraguan
                    Foreign Minister<note n="4" xml:id="d727fn4">Manuel Cordero Reyes.</note> that
                    the proposed increase in the rate of exchange for the payment of import duties
                    which would require that import duties prescribed in Schedule I of the trade
                    agreement be paid in cordobas at the official rate of exchange for the United
                    States dollar involves the important question of the effect of the proposed
                    measure upon the trade agreement. The Department hopes that action in regard to
                    the measure will be deferred until the views of this Government with respect
                    thereto can be communicated to the Nicaraguan Government. The Department hopes
                    to be able to transmit such views within a few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
